parameters:
I had to wait forever, but I finally got inside the shop.
With it being this crowded, I wish they would take
reservations.

I had to wait an incredibly long time, but I finally made it
inside the shop. With it being this crowded, I wish they
would take reservations.

I had to wait forever, but I finally got inside the shop.
With it being this crowded, I wish they would take
reservations.

Well done for coming, Karin! Would you like some sweets? We
also have Inari sushi!

To be able to eat such sweet confections... I'm glad I've
lived this long.

It's my first time here, but it feels like my tongue is
melting...\I[15]I wonder if I can take some home?

I have a real sweet tooth. The sweets at this tea house are
exceptional.

Before this shop was built, this place was just a field... I
wonder when the house was built? It's quite mysterious...

Wow...! The wild strawberries and sugar are intertwined,
making it so delicious\I[15]

I'm glad the children are happy too. The Miko who
owns the shop is cute with her fake ears, it's a very nice
place.

"That was really delicious I'll definitely come to eat here
again."
We look forward to your next visit.

...Good grief, I never expected so many people to come. At
this rate, I won't last a week after opening.

Masaki-sensei's sweets are exotic and very delicious. Since
it's a novel food that hasn't been seen in Japan before,
it's no wonder so many people come.

Right!? I learned it when I traveled abroad long ago. Over
there, they have a confection called "sweets". I thought it
would sell well in Japan! Nyahaha!

...Now that the work is done, can we also have some of
Masaki-chan's sweets?

What? Have you both been holding back until now? Very well,
very well It's my way of thanking you for your help!
Yay, I'm so happy Let's dig in!
Oh... Delicious!? What is this! It's so sweet and exquisite!

Chomp chomp...! (Amazing...! This is the best sweet I've
ever had!)

Mufufu! Isn't it, isn't it? It's made by whipping milk with
sugar. It's my favorite food, having lived for over a
thousand years\I[15]

Really, it feels like my tongue is melting with sweetness in
my mouth...! I've never eaten such delicious sweets before

Munch munch... (So this is a Western confection... Hmm, the
world is vast indeed...)
If you'd like, there's more where that came from?
Hooray! Then please, I'd like some more!

Momiji-dono, I am grateful. I would like some more as
well...
Ah... Satisfaction guaranteed Thank you for the meal\I[15]

Indeed! Both of you ate so well! It makes me, the maker,
very happy

So, why did both of you come to this tea house? Did you have
something to ask the master?

Right, right, Masaki-chan, do you know about the Divine
Threefold Sword?

We heard it's a divine weapon to slay demons, and we've been
searching for it.

Hmm... The Divine Threefold Sword? That is indeed a
formidable weapon. For demons, it's an absolutely detestable
divine artifact. If you manage to obtain it, it will
undoubtedly become a power to annihilate the war demons.

--! It's good to know you're aware of it! Where can we find
this sword?

The [Forest of Spirits]--it's sealed there. It belongs
to me.

Yes, it's a sword with which I have a connection. However,
it might be a bit rusty since it's been neglected in the
treasury for hundreds of years.

Alright, there's no time like the present. Let's head to
this Forest of Spirits right away!
And where exactly is this Forest of Spirits located?

The location is in Kazusa, southeast from here in Edo. It's
a forest within a forest, an untouched natural area where
people cannot easily tread.

Kazusa, huh... Then we'll need a travel permit to get past
the checkpoint. We're off to the magistrate's office, Karin.

Eh...? The magistrate's office? I... had a terrible
experience after being caught once, so I honestly don't want
to go...

Even so, without a travel permit, we'd be breaking through
the checkpoint illegally, right? Do you want to become a
criminal and be chased by the magistrate's office again?
Ah... Can't be helped... I'll go as well...

Master, may I accompany them? I want to be of help to the
two of them...

Indeed. Help Karin and Yugiri, Momiji. I'll switch the shop
to reservation-only, so I should be able to manage by myself
for a while.

--Karin, Yugiri, and Momiji headed to the magistrate's
office!

Who goes there? What business do you have at the
magistrate's office?
Pardon me--I am Yugiri, the leader of the Iga ninja group.

It has been a while, Tamba-dono. Today, I have come to
request a travel permit to Kazusa.

It's just... we absolutely must go to the Forest of
Apparitions in Kazusa. Please grant us this request...

Karin. I've heard about your exploits since returning to
Edo. The night hawk disappearance case, the courtesan
disappearance case at the pleasure quarters--you've secretly
solved those two incidents in Edo.

You've also defeated bandits and demon armies outside of
Edo. The quarrel with Mouse Komachi is old news now. Now
that Karin is part of the Iga ninja group, we are all
servants under the same shogunate. There is no reason for
the magistrate's office to refuse.

I couldn't believe it when they said demons were involved,
but if the elder statesman says so, there must be no
mistake. Shall I prepare three travel permits then?

It seems you were wary of the magistrate's office, but
instead you were praised.

Yes. It's a bit surprising considering we were at odds not
too long ago... ehehe...

I'm glad we were able to get the travel permits without any
trouble.

Yes. Since we received three permits, I'll hand one out to
each of us.

Now we're all set to head to the Forest of Spirits.
Since it's already getting dark today, let's meet tomorrow
at the checkpoint east of Fukagawa.

Understood. Then tomorrow at the checkpoint east of
Fukagawa--
--Karin parted ways with Yugiri and Momiji.

(Ugh...? Suddenly feeling an urge... Maybe I ate too much
sweet stuff? I need to hurry home.)
--Karin hurried back home at a brisk pace.
Huh...? There's something lying on the side of the road...

A travel permit just lying here? Heh, fortune smiles upon
me. I'll be taking this for myself

Thank you for helping me, Karin-chan. I'll accompany you
when we go to the forest of spirits.

I'm glad the children are happy too. The Miko who
runs the store is cute with her fake ears, it's a very nice
shop.

Even an old guy like me loves sweets. The treats here are
seriously delicious. Try some, you'll be blown away.

Sugar used to be a luxury item in the past, but now that
it's become accessible even to commoners, we truly live in
better times, don't we?

I'm glad the children were pleased. The Miko who

nice place.
